# Jongara Flutter Architecture Guidelines

This project follows a clean architecture approach with MVVM pattern. Adhere to these guidelines for all development work:

## Project Structure
- Maintain the layered architecture: core → data → domain → presentation
- Each layer should only depend on layers below it
- Presentation layer must not directly access data layer repositories

## State Management
- Use setState for simple state management
- Avoid external state management libraries like Riverpod, BLoC, or Provider
- Keep state management simple and contained within widgets when possible

## Code Style
- Follow Flutter's style guide and best practices
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep functions small and focused on a single responsibility
- Document complex logic with clear comments

## Data Models
- Define clear model classes with appropriate constructors
- Avoid using freezed package or part syntax
- Keep models immutable when possible

## Storage
- Use SharedPreferences for local data persistence
- No external database dependencies required

## UI/UX
- Maintain the "Warm Wood, Carved Jade" color palette defined in theme constants
- Follow the zen-like, minimalist aesthetic throughout the app
- Ensure responsive layouts that work across different screen sizes
- Implement smooth animations for tile movements and transitions

## Assets
- No local image assets or custom fonts required
- No network image loading required